espeare exerted on mass entertainment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEnglish dramaxHistory and criticismx17th century. 0aEnglish dramaxHistory and criticismxEarly modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600. 0aEnglish dramay17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish dramayEarly modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600xHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226445731423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226445731.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles